      "content": "It's okay to feel like life is empty and you're waiting for something to happen to make things better. Sometimes, the pain can feel unbearable, and it might seem like there's no way out. But remember, even in the darkest times, there can be a glimmer of hope. Talking to someone, even if it feels futile, can sometimes help you find a way through the darkness. It's also okay to take things one step at a time. You don't have to figure everything out right now. Be kind to yourself and try to find small moments of peace, even if they feel insignificant. You're not alone, and there are people who want to help you.",
      "source": "target",
